children.name: Document Heading
children.characters: How to contribute to the design system

children.name: Text
children.characters:
Does anything else exist that could solve the problem?

The primary thing we want to avoid is adding something new where existing component or design pattern might solve the problem.

Can the component you’re creating be re-used elsewhere in Pendo?

One-offs for specific use cases are OK, but do consider if your work or parts of it could be re-used in any way. If so, then add it to the library!

children.name: Section Title / Heading 2
children.characters: Ok! Which library should I add to?

children.name: Text
children.characters:
If it is a base style, variable, token, icon or illustration:

Add it to Prism Foundations.

children.name: Text
children.characters:
If it is globally applicable or generic component (like buttons, cards, modals—basic UI elements):

Add it here, to Prism Central Components (this library is reflected in a central repo for engineers to use, see Storybook).

children.name: Text
children.characters:
If the component isn’t globally applicable, but you think another team could leverage the work you’ve done:

Add it to the Prism Shared Components library. This library contains elements that will have been built, but aren’t yet documented in Storybook.

children.name: Section Title / Heading 2
children.characters: How do I add a component?

children.name: Text
children.characters: Starting from the Prism main file you want to contribute to (see above):

children.name: Text
children.characters: This gives you a workspace separate from the main file. From here you can create / modify components.

children.name: Text
children.characters:
Invite a group of testers into your branched file so that they can test your new component.

Testing Tips:
Share your test on #design-system or #crit channel to gather feedback or in an Open Studio session!
There is a “Testing Playground” page in the file that you and your testers can use to test your new component

children.name: Text
children.characters:
Invite a group of testers into your branched file so that they can test your new component.

Testing Tips:
Share your test on #design-system or #crit channel to gather feedback or in an Open Studio session!
There is a “Testing Playground” page in the file that you and your testers can use to test your new component

Should I do user testing?
If it’s a workflow or mental model breaking change, then definitely test.
If it’s a cosmetic change that’s an industry standard, you can err on the side of not testing, unless:
In Pendo, we have a different use cases for the same patterns
Test the use cases against each other to choose one use case to use the pattern for
Different industry standards for a pattern
Figure out which standard works better for Pendo.
Small things
If we have a lot of small changes incoming, we might batch test them together for better use of testing resource!

If in doubt, reach out on #user_research channel!

children.name: Text
children.characters:
Add reviewers and add a note for context:

🐞 If it is a small change, like a small modification or bug fix:
Add one reviewer from the list

🏗️ If it is a large change, like adding a new component:
Add at least two reviewers.

Once a review has been completed, your changes will be merged back into the main file and published for all designers to access! You will be notified when your component is merged into main.

children.name: Text
children.characters: Be sure to let everyone know about your contribution, so that designers can take advantage of your brilliant work! Post in the #design_system channel, and let everyone know in our Monday Open Office and / or throughout the week in crit jams or open studios!
